lding and vice-versa. Where much has been made of the racial dynamics of US colonialism in the region, McKenna emphasizes capitalist practices and design ideals-giving us a fresh and nuanced understanding of the American occupation of the Philippines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aCity planningzPhilippineszBaguioxHistory. 0aIgorot (Philippine people)zPhilippineszBenguet (Province)xHistory. 4aDaniel Burnham. 4aPhilippines. 4aProgressivism. 4aUnited States imperialism. 4acapitalism. 4acolonialism. 4ahill station. 4aurban planning. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226417936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226417936.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles